author: Inside Edition
description: There is a growing mystery surrounding Diane Keaton's death. How did someone so vibrant succumb to pneumonia at age 79? The iconic actress was at home in Brentwood when a 911 call was made. Inside Edition spoke to New York emergency medicine doctor Tucker Woods. With Keaton's family's announcement that she "passed away from pneumonia," older Americans are worried. Doctor Woods recommends anyone over the age of 50 should get the pneumococcal vaccine.
title: Older Americans Wonder How To Protect Themselves From Pneumonia

author: Inside Edition
description: The humble hero who saved a family of five from their blazing home and then took off before they could thank him has been found. ER nurse Nick Arreola says he saw the fire as he was driving home at 3 a.m. after he finished his shift in Arizona. Arreola got the family to safety, but he disappeared before they could get his name. He says he'd forgotten his phone that day and was concerned about being out of touch with his pregnant fiancée. Now, the family is thanking him for coming to their rescue.
title: Humble Hero Reunites With Family He Saved From House Fire

author: Inside Edition
description: Police say Crystal Tadlock was stopped for speeding and erratic driving when she said "I’m a f****** nurse, and when you come through my hospital, don't, I'll let you die." Tadlock works in the intensive care unit where patients' lives are on the line. Her bosses swiftly gave her the ax. Four years prior, Tadlock was named one of America's extraordinary nurses for her work during the pandemic. She is being charged with "driving while intoxicated" after cops say she failed the field sobriety test.
title: Arrested ICU Nurse Tells Cop 'I'll Let You Die'

author: Inside Edition
description: Britney Spears is fighting back against her ex-husband Kevin Federline and his explosive new-tell book. Spears posted a slew of dancing videos overnight fuming. In his new book, "You Thought You Knew," Federline alleges Spears did "cocaine” while breastfeeding their two sons, among other claims. Spears is firing back saying she feels demoralized and that she has "pleaded and screamed to have a life with her sons," but that they have witnessed a lack of respect by their father towards Spears.
title: Britney Spears Fires Back After Ex-Husband’s Tell-All Book

author: Inside Edition
description: Supermodel Gigi Hadid caused a sensation this year in all white. She also hit the runway, swathed in a coat of pink flowers. Hadid is Bradley Cooper's girlfriend. Cooper's ex-girlfriend, supermodel Irina Shayk was also on the runway. In a Victoria's Secret first, model Jasmine Tookers opened the show 9 months pregnant, and basked in the spotlight cradling her baby bump. Another first: WNBA superstar Angel Reese became the first professional athlete to appear in the show.
title: Victoria's Secret Angels Fly High At This Years Show

author: Inside Edition
description: A quick-acting security officer noticed the woman about to walk right in front of an oncoming tram and yanked her out of its path. It happened in the Turkish city of Kayseri. Officials say the woman was wearing headphones, but the officer was monitoring the yellow safety line. While she was looking in the opposite direction of the oncoming tram, she didn't get by this vigilant officer. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Woman Nearly Walks In Front Of Tram Until Stopped By Vigilant Officer

author: Inside Edition
description: Dick Harpootlian defended Alex Murdaugh at his trial in 2023 for the murder of his wife, Maggie, and son, Paul.
title: Alex Murdaugh's Attorney Speaks Out About New Hulu Series #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: You can find Anna Possi in the same place she's been for the past 65 years, behind the counter at her bar in Nebbuino, Italy, serving coffee. Coming up on her 101st birthday, Possi is recognized as the longest serving barista. She opened her bar with her husband, but she's been running it since he died 51 years ago. She's outlived most of her original clientele, but she says now she gets to serve tourists and new customers. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 100-Year-Old Woman Is Longest-Serving Barista In Italy

author: Inside Edition
description: A Colorado meteorologist, fearful for her life, says she's been stalked for three years by an obsessed viewer. Kylie Bearse of Denver station KDVR opened up about her traumatic experience. She went into more detail in an interview with NewsNation's Ashley Banfield. Bearse says the man has violated restraining orders 53 times in two months. She is also upset that the suspect is not facing felony charges and is out on bond wearing an ankle monitor.
title: Denver Meteorologist Says She Is Being Stalked By Obsessed Viewer

author: Inside Edition
description: The IE team is throwing it back to the soundtrack of our first day on the job.
title: What Was The #Topsong On Your First Day At Your Job? #shorts
